\lambda_k = 1, \quad \mu_k = 2k-1 \quad \text{and} \quad g(x) = x\sqrt{2}^{-x}.
\int_0^\infty x\sqrt{2}^{-x} x^{s-1} dx = \int_0^\infty \sqrt{2}^{-x} x^{(s+1)-1} dx = \frac{1}{(1/2\log 2)^{s+1}}\Gamma(s+1).
\sum_{k\ge 1} \frac{\lambda_k}{\mu_k^s} = \sum_{k\ge 1} \frac{1}{(2k-1)^s} = (1-2^{-s})\zeta(s).
Q(s) = \frac{1}{(1/2 \log 2)^{s+1}} (1-2^{-s}) \Gamma(s+1) \zeta(s).
